HEADWORD: Selenhydric
<hw>Sel`en*hy"dric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, hydrogen selenide,
<chform>H2Se</chform>, regarded as an acid analogous to sulphydric
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
